Great little bar & grill. Located in the French Quarters. Almost past this little gem up. A local told me I could get a club sandwich here. I walked in & right away I felt like family with a few businessmen. Then I realized why I felt so welcome.  The bartender Natacha was the magic to this little Irish pub.  Her positive bubbling attitude was remarkable. Greeting everyone of her customers by name.  Her smile ran for a mile.  Her people skills were naturally mastered.  Only seen that talent in Fortune 500 trained sales people.  And by the way the club sandwich was great. But I didn’t care if it was are not. Just felt at home.  Thanks Natacha for your superior service.  (Kiss Food Critic) FB.

What can I say about the Copper Monkey Grill? It is a loud, kind of old-style dive bar and grill. They have a decent but not a great selection of liquors. And, it is crowded without really enough staff to keep up. I suppose if we sat at the bar and not at a table it may have been different.  We ordered drinks and food from the bartender. It arrived pretty quickly. My son and I both had Oyster Po-Boys and my wife had a salad. How was the Po-Boy? It was not the best I've had but far from the worst. I like crusty bread on Po-Boys, but here the bread is pretty soft. The oysters were breaded but did not have much taste. Well, nothing a little hot sauce can't fix.  I did particularly like the tater tots they served with the sandwich. My son had their sweet potato fries and also raved about them.  In my opinion, they were generous with their pours. But, what do I know?
